## 1. GRAPH VISUALIZATION

### vis.js Network — Your Current Library
- **Official examples gallery:** https://visjs.github.io/vis-network/examples/
  - This is gold. Every edge style, node shape, color group, clustering behavior — all shown with live code. Spend an hour here before touching any styling code.
- **Full network documentation:** https://visjs.github.io/vis-network/docs/
  - Node groups are the key feature for Fractal — you can assign nodes to groups and style each group differently. This is exactly how you'd color domain nodes vs the grey emergent node.
- **CodeSandbox examples:** https://codesandbox.io/examples/package/vis-network
  - Live editable examples including a Vue + Flask integration that's very close to Fractal's stack

### D3.js Force Graph — The Upgrade Path
If you ever outgrow vis.js or want more visual control, D3 is the next level. It's harder but gives you pixel-perfect control over everything.
- **D3 force directed graph:** https://d3js.org/d3-force
  - The physics engine behind most interactive knowledge graphs on the web
- **3D force graph (vasturiano):** https://github.com/vasturiano/3d-force-graph
  - Someone built a beautiful 3D version of exactly what Fractal does using D3 + ThreeJS. Has React bindings. This is worth studying deeply — it's basically a more advanced Fractal.
- **LLM + D3 force graph (almost exactly Fractal):** https://medium.com/@junjunzaragosa2309/using-llm-to-generate-data-for-d3-js-force-directed-graph-c490382d1172
  - A developer built the exact same concept — LLM generates nodes and links, D3 renders them. Their source code is on GitHub: https://github.com/jzaragosa06/fdg-and-ai and live demo on Render. Study this carefully.

### Obsidian Graph View — Design Inspiration
Obsidian is a note-taking app but its graph view is exactly the aesthetic Fractal should aim for. It's the most beloved graph UI in the developer world.
- **Obsidian graph view:** https://obsidian.md
  - Download and use it for free. Study how nodes cluster, how clicking feels, how the physics behaves. This is your design reference.
- **InfraNodus — AI + graph:** https://infranodus.com
  - A tool that adds AI-powered gap detection to knowledge graphs. Very close to Fractal's vision. Not open source but useful to understand what the product looks like when it's mature.

