## 2. LLM BACKEND

### Groq — Your Production API
- **Official quickstart:** https://console.groq.com/docs/quickstart
  - Get an API key and make your first call in under 10 minutes. Use `llama-3.3-70b-versatile` as the model — it's their best free-tier model right now.
- **JSON mode on Groq:** Pass `response_format: {"type": "json_object"}` in your API call — Groq supports this natively, which means cleaner structured output for Fractal maps without extra parsing work.

### Ollama — Your Dev Environment
- **Structured outputs official docs:** https://docs.ollama.com/capabilities/structured-outputs
  - Ollama now natively supports JSON schema enforcement. Pass your Fractal JSON schema directly to the `format` parameter and the model is *forced* to return valid JSON matching your schema. This is huge — no more broken JSON crashing your graph.
- **Practical JSON guide:** https://voipnuggets.com/2025/12/30/how-to-get-structured-json-responses-from-a-llm-using-ollama/
  - Short, practical, shows both simple JSON mode and strict schema enforcement
- **Production-grade structured output pipeline:** https://markaicode.com/ollama-structured-output-pipeline/
  - The honest guide — covers what breaks at scale (6% failure rate at 10k calls/day), how to add Pydantic validation + retry loops, and when to switch to grammar-constrained generation. Read before you go to production.

### Instructor — The Pro Tool for Structured Output
- **Instructor + Ollama:** https://python.useinstructor.com/integrations/ollama/
  - Instructor is a Python library that wraps Ollama/OpenAI and guarantees structured output using Pydantic models. It adds automatic retry logic when the model returns bad JSON. For Fractal's backend this is a 10-line upgrade that makes your JSON output rock solid. Highly recommended.

